                                Say

        The Say program enables you to type text into a window and hear it
spoken back to you through the speaker on your TV or monitor. When you
double-click on the Say icon, two windows are opened. The top window is the
Phoneme window, and below that is the Input window. Select the Input
window, and type in your text followed by a Return. If you reach the edge
of the window and you haven't finished typing, don't press Return as the
text will wrap around to the next line automatically. When you press Return
the text is displayed phonetically in the Phoneme window and spoken from
your TV or monitor (assuming you have the stereo output connectors of your
Amiga plugged in). You may have to spell the word phonetically to get the
speech to sound more natural.

        There a number of options which enable you to change the character
of the speech output. Select the Input window and type one of the following
codes followed by Return. From then on any text typed in will be spoken
with the corresponding character.

                        -m male voice

                        -f female voice

                        -r robot inflection

                        -n natural inflection

                        -p Alter the pitch

                        -s Alters the speed

                Pitch -p <number> between (65 and 320)

                Speed -s <number> between (40 and 400)


        Workbench 3 doesn't come supplied with the Say utility.



